Create Tables: Create two Hive tables to store the student information and their marks.

sql
Copy
Edit
CREATE TABLE StudentInfo (
    StuID INT,
    Name STRING,
    Branch STRING
)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED
FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
STORED AS TEXTFILE;

CREATE TABLE StudentMarks (
    StuID INT,
    Subject STRING,
    Marks INT
)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED
FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
STORED AS TEXTFILE;
Load Data: Load data into both tables. You should have the data files (CSV or text files) stored on HDFS.

sql
Copy
Edit
LOAD DATA INPATH '/user/hive/warehouse/student_info.csv' INTO TABLE StudentInfo;
LOAD DATA INPATH '/user/hive/warehouse/student_marks.csv' INTO TABLE StudentMarks;
Join Tables: Join the two tables on StuID and filter students with marks greater than 80.

sql
Copy
Edit
SELECT s.StuID, s.Name, s.Branch, m.Subject, m.Marks
FROM StudentInfo s
JOIN StudentMarks m ON s.StuID = m.StuID
WHERE m.Marks > 80;
